Privacy Policy – Radio Al-Salam App
At the Radio Al-Salam App, we respect your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal information. This policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your data when you use the app.

Information We Collect
Information Collected Automatically: When you use the app, we may automatically collect certain technical information such as your device type, operating system, IP address, and general usage data to improve app performance and user experience.

Personal Information: We do not collect any personally identifiable information such as your name, email address, or phone number.

How We Use Information
The information we collect is used solely to enhance the app's functionality, analyze performance, resolve technical issues, and improve your listening experience. We do not use your information for marketing purposes, nor do we sell it to third parties.

Sharing of Information
We do not share user information with third parties, except as required by law or to protect our legal rights.

App Permissions
The app may request certain permissions that are necessary for its core functions, such as internet access for streaming radio content. We do not access or store any sensitive data unrelated to the app’s operation.

Data Security
We implement reasonable security measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, alteration, or disclosure.

Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted within the app or on the official app listing page.

